Geraldine Jones, 36, of Gary, Indiana has been charged with murder, kidnapping and criminal confinement in the death of Samantha Fleming . 
  Police say Jones pretended to be a child services worker in order to steal Fleming's daughter and claim the child as her own after faking a pregnancy . 
  Fleming's body was found in a garbage bag doused in bleach in the home she shared with her daughter and boyfriend . 
  She was lured from her home by Jones and her daughter Serenity was with her . 
  Jones allegedly told Fleming she was with the Department of Child Services but never worked for the agency . 
  She is accused of killing Fleming and taking the 17-day-old baby . 
 